description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare Assistant (Nights) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 positions available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 30 hours (worked over 3 nights)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 3. £17,051- £21,027 per annum according to skills and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Various locations within the community and Compton Hall&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compton Care seeks 3 highly motivated and experienced Healthcare Assistant to join our established Community Care Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be providing accessible, innovative and influential care that creates extraordinary experiences for the people living with complex and incurable conditions in our communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will participate in assessing, planning and delivering social care to patients with a life limiting illness mainly in the home environment by working in partnership with the patient and their carers and collaboratively with internal colleagues and the external health community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide emotional and psychological support to the patient, their family and friends and aim to inspire and encourage others by acting as a guardian for Compton standards and reputation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential skills and experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be qualified at NVQ Level 3 in Care or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have at least two years previous experience of delivering nursing care in a health and social care setting, preferably the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Has a full driving licence and use of a car to travel between patient homes and Compton Care Sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be able to demonstrates the ability to work unsupervised in the patient’s home&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be able to demonstrates clear and legible written communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
